Ahmet Davutolu is a Turkish politician and scholar who served as Prime Minister of Turkey from 2014 to 2016. He held this position for a total of two terms. In addition to that, he served as Turkey's Minister of Foreign Affairs, and he is now a member of the governing Justice and Development Party (AKP). His concept of "strategic depth," which highlights Turkey's historical and cultural links to the area, is especially well-known for its role in his crucial role in creating Turkey's foreign policy. He is well-known for this position. 